{
  "title": "Benchmarking Edge Runtimes Using FastAPI with Python 3.12+",
  "summary": "This explainer demonstrates how to measure and compare the performance of your FastAPI applications when deployed as edge runtimes using Python 3.12+.",
  "key_points": [
    "Understand the importance of benchmarking edge runtimes for FastAPI applications",
    "Prepare an example FastAPI application for benchmarking",
    "Install and set up a profiling tool (e.g., cProfile, line_profiler, or pyperfstat)",
    "Run the profiler on the FastAPI application to generate performance reports",
    "Analyze the results and make improvements to optimize the edge runtime performance"
  ],
  "code_examples": [
    {
      "language": "Python",
      "code": "```python\n\nfrom fastapi import FastAPI\nimport uvicorn\n\napp = FastAPI()\n\n@app.get('/')\ndef main():\n    return {'message': 'Hello, World!'}\n\nif __name__ == "__main__":\n    uvicorn.run(app, host='0.0.0.0', port=8000)\n```"
    },
    {
      "language": "Python",
      "code": "```python\n\nimport cProfile\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    pr = cProfile.Profile()\n    pr.runcall(app.asgi().asgi_app())\n    pr.print_stats(sort=cProfile.SortKey.TIME)\n```"
    }
  ],
  "version_notes": [
    "Python 3.12+ is required for this explainer due to the use of FastAPI and modern profiling tools.",
    "FastAPI version 0.74.0 or higher recommended."
  ],
  "caveats": [
    "Profiling can consume a significant amount of resources, so ensure you have enough memory and processing power available.",
    "The profiler's output may vary depending on the selected tool and the specific configuration used.",
    "Optimizing your FastAPI application for performance should not compromise its readability or maintainability."
  ]
}
